Sentencas: This paper presents a multisource, multiconverter power system for electrically propelled unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) with a focus on promoting fuel cell health.
Titulo: Multiconverter System Design for Fuel Cell Buffering and Diagnostics Under UAV Load Profiles

Sentencas: Linearized multiconverter system analysis and the two extra element theorem (2EET) inform a system design for fuel cell current buffering and integral diagnostics.
Titulo: Multiconverter System Design for Fuel Cell Buffering and Diagnostics Under UAV Load Profiles

Sentencas: Integral diagnostics is in situ impedance spectroscopy achieved by controlling the power system to superpose a frequency-swept excitation current at the fuel cell terminals.
Titulo: Multiconverter System Design for Fuel Cell Buffering and Diagnostics Under UAV Load Profiles

Sentencas: An experimental system demonstrates hybridization of a solid-oxide fuel cell (SOFC) with a lead-acid battery having suitable current buffering and integral diagnostics performance under UAV load profiles.
Titulo: Multiconverter System Design for Fuel Cell Buffering and Diagnostics Under UAV Load Profiles

Sentencas: Experimental behavior is demonstrated with an electrically emulated SOFC stack or reference simulator.
Titulo: Multiconverter System Design for Fuel Cell Buffering and Diagnostics Under UAV Load Profiles

Sentencas: Impedance spectroscopy data measured during run-time clearly indicate both degradation and recovery phenomena in the SOFC.
Titulo: Multiconverter System Design for Fuel Cell Buffering and Diagnostics Under UAV Load Profiles
